@hello! I know it's odd to ask you a question so close to what you were just told, but if you can tell me where I can find you in this universe...
<|man in the shadows|>
@hello indeed. You're right, it is odd to ask. This universe is in no better condition for its inhabitants than it was when I arrived. Perhaps I could learn something about what my feeble human mind has considered a universe if only it could grasp where the rules of logic might have once held sway.
<|darkness|>
As I feared I cannot help you now, my friend. It is not a question of understanding the mechanics of something so petty and temporary as an afterlife. We can only observe the world from this plane of existence; there are far too many distractions to concern ourselves with the truth beyond the veil.
I am sorry for your pains.
